  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Introduction"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Big advantage of UTF is that we can create a wrap function for an module."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "We will use -wrap from GHS (Green Hills)"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/6.%20Creating%20Wrap%20functions/image-2023-3-25_17-36-37.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/6. Creating Wrap functions/image-2023-3-25_17-36-37.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Steps to create Wrap functions"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Step 1: In the Module Test case Cmake we need to specify which function we need to Wrap"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "In our example we are going to wrap Psc_ShutDownRequest API"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/6.%20Creating%20Wrap%20functions/image-2023-3-25_17-39-3.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/6. Creating Wrap functions/image-2023-3-25_17-39-3.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Step 2: In Module wrap file (Modulename_Wrap.c) define the wrap function like below"
    },
    {
      "type": "panel",
      "panel_type": "info",
      "title": "",
      "content": "Use __wrap_ in front of function definition"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "When our code calls Psc_ShutDownRequest API, instead of actual API this wrapper API (__wrap_Psc_ShutDownRequest) will be called"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/6.%20Creating%20Wrap%20functions/image-2023-3-25_17-41-49.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/6. Creating Wrap functions/image-2023-3-25_17-41-49.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Step 3: In case if we need to call the actual API inside the wrap API we can as in below example"
    },
    {
      "type": "panel",
      "panel_type": "info",
      "title": "",
      "content": "To call the original API we need to use __real_"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/6.%20Creating%20Wrap%20functions/image-2023-3-25_17-46-54.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/6. Creating Wrap functions/image-2023-3-25_17-46-54.png"
    }
  ],
